The paper deals with problems related to graph theory and optimization, specifically the problem of minimizing branching vertices in distance-preserving subgraphs. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). However, given the focus on graph theory and optimization, cs.DM and cs.DS are the most likely sub-categories. The use of interval graphs and strong products of interval graphs also suggests a possible connection to cs.CG. The mention of NP-hardness and polynomial time algorithms further supports the likelihood of cs.DM and cs.DS. Finally, the use of all-pairs distance-preserving subgraphs and branching vertices suggests a possible connection to cs.GT and cs.NA, respectively.
